Unlike conventional open-circuit scuba systems that continuously vent gas into the environment, NEREUS-H1 utilizes a closed-loop architecture that recirculates breathing gases while removing carbon dioxide and replenishing oxygen.

Primary objectives:

• Maximize breathing efficiency
• Reduce gas consumption
• Increase mission endurance
• Improve operator safety
